## OPENING PRAYER

IM: (_If a Chaplain is present—_) Companion Chaplain.

IMor: _
Chap: Companions, bow your heads.

Note: I._M. uncovers head, and all Companions assume
  Position of Reverence.

>>> May our Supreme Benefactor have us in his holy
  keeping; may he ever direct us to such measures as he
  himself shall approve and be pleased to bless. May our
  sanctuary be the pride of the worthy, the resort and seat
  of all moral virtues, the asylum of the oppressed, until
  the last of time shall bury the empires of the world in
  ruin. {{endnote-ref rm-divine-pronouns}}

Response: So mote it be.

## DECLARATION & ATTENDING THE ALTAR

IM: In the name of God and Adoniram, I declare |
   {{blank 6em 4em}} Council No. {{blank 2em}}, Cryptic Masons opened <|
   on the Royal Master Degree in form. (_I._M. recovers._)
   Companion Conductor of the Council, display the Great
   Lights.
Note: C._C. advances to altar, squaring corners, opens the
   Volume of the Sacred Law to 1_Kings_6:27, places the
   Square and Compasses on the right hand page, and
   salutes the I._M. as a R._M., and returns.

## INFORMING THE SENTINEL

IM: Companion Captain of the Guard, inform the Sentinel.
CG: Companion Steward, inform the Sentinel.

Note: Without saluting, the Steward goes to the door
   and gives ●●● ●●● ●● to call up the Sentinel. |
   The Sentinel acknowledges by returning the same
   ●●● ●●● ●●.

%PAGE
Stew: (_Opens door._) Companion Sentinel, this Council is
   opened on the Royal Master Degree in form.

Note: Steward closes door and seals it with ●. Sentinel
   acknowledges by returning the same ●.

Stew: (_Returns to his station, faces C._G. and salutes as a
   R._M._) Companion Captain of the Guard, your order has
   been obeyed.
CG: (_Salutes I._M. as a R._M._) Illustrious Master, your order
   has been obeyed.

## FLAG CEREMONY

Note: This flag ceremony shall be given the first time the
   Council is opened for a meeting. After opening, and
   before the craft is seated, the Illustrious Master shall
   remove his hat and say:

IM: Companions, salute the Flag of our Country, emblem of
   liberty, equality, and fraternity, principles worthy the
   devotion of every Mason.

Note: At the command "salute" all give the civilian salute
   of right hand over heart, facing the flag. The I._M.
   may continue and proceed by leading the craft in the
   Pledge of Allegiance.

IM: ●.

